# Optics Formula Reference
*Based on NBEO Part 1 Geometrical and Visual Optics Material*

## 1. Basic Terms and Concepts
**Snell's Law**
$$n(\sin\theta) = n'(\sin\theta')$$

---

## 2. Refraction at Spherical Surfaces
**Surface Power ($F$) & Focal Lengths ($f, f'$)**
* **Secondary Focal Length:**
    $$F = \frac{n'}{f'}$$
* **Primary Focal Length:**
    $$F = -\frac{n}{f}$$
* **Surface Power (using Radius $r$):**
    $$F = \frac{n' - n}{r}$$

---

## 3. The Vergence Relationship
**Vergence Equation**
$$L' = L + F$$

* **Object Vergence ($L$):** $L = n / l$
* **Image Vergence ($L'$):** $L' = n' / l'$
* **Lateral Magnification ($M_L$):**
    $$M_L = \frac{L}{L'}$$

---

## 4. Thin Lenses
**Lens Power & Magnification**
* **Nominal Power:**
    $$F_T = F_1 + F_2$$
* **Lateral Magnification (Lens in medium):**
    $$M_L = \frac{L}{L'}$$
* **Lateral Magnification (Lens in air):**
    $$M_L = \frac{l'}{l}$$
* **Newton's Relation:**
    $$xx' = f^2$$

---

## 5. Optical Systems with Multiple Surfaces
**System Magnification**
* **Two Lenses:** $\text{Total } M_L = (M_{L1}) \times (M_{L2})$
* **Two Surfaces:** $\text{Total } M_L = (M_{L1}) \times (M_{L2})$

---

## 6. Thick Lenses
**Vertex & Equivalent Powers**
* **Back Vertex Power ($F_v$):**
    $$F_v = \frac{F_1}{1 - (t/n)F_1} + F_2$$
* **Front Vertex Power ($F_n$):**
    $$F_n = \frac{F_2}{1 - (t/n)F_2} + F_1$$
* **Equivalent Power ($F_e$):**
    $$F_e = F_1 + F_2 - \frac{t}{n} F_1 F_2$$

**Principal Plane Locations**
* **$A_1H$:**
    $$A_1H = \frac{(t/n) F_2}{F_e}$$
* **$A_2H'$:**
    $$A_2H' = \frac{-(t/n) F_1}{F_e}$$

---

## 9. Cylindrical Lenses and the Correction of Astigmatism
* **Oblique Meridian Power:**
    $$F_{\theta} = (F_{cyl}) \sin^2\theta$$
* **Spherical Equivalent:**
    $$SE = \text{spherical correction} + \frac{\text{cylindrical correction}}{2}$$

---

## 10. Prisms
**Prism Formulas**
* **Minimum Deviation (Thin Prism):**
    $$d_{min} = \alpha(n - 1)$$
* **Prism Power (Displacement):**
    $$P = 100 \left( \frac{x}{y} \right)$$
* **Prentice's Rule:**
    $$P = (c)(F)$$

---

## 11. Depth of Field
**Resolution Limit**
* **Radius of Airyâ€™s Disk:**
    $$\theta = \frac{1.22 \lambda}{d}$$

---

## 12. Magnification and Low Vision Devices
** magnifiers & Telescopes**
* **Equivalent Viewing Power (Add/Cap):**
    $$EVP = (M) (\text{add power})$$
* **Effective Magnification (25cm ref):**
    $$M_{25} = \frac{F}{4}$$
* **Telescope Angular Magnification ($M_{ang}$):**
    $$M_{ang} = -\frac{F_2}{F_1}$$
    $$M_{ang} = \frac{1}{1 - dF_1}$$
    $$M_{ang} = \frac{\text{entrance pupil diameter}}{\text{exit pupil diameter}}$$

---

## 13. Retinal Image Size
**Spectacle Magnification**
* **General Formula:**
    $$M_{spect} = (M_{power}) \times (M_{shape})$$
* **Expanded Formula:**
    $$M_{spect} = \left[ \frac{1}{1 - dF_v} \right] \left[ \frac{1}{1 - (t/n)F_1} \right]$$

---

## 14. Reflection
**Mirrors**
* **Power (using Radius $r$):**
    $$F = -\frac{2}{r}$$
* **Power (using Focal Length $f'$):**
    $$F = -\frac{1}{f'}$$
* **Radius Relationship:**
    $$r = 2f'$$
* **Image Location:**
    $$L' = -\frac{1}{l'}$$
* **Magnification:**
    $$M_L = -\frac{l'}{l}$$

**Reflectance**
* **Fraction Reflected ($R$):**
    $$R = \left[ \frac{n' - n}{n' + n} \right]^2$$
* **Ideal AR Coating Index:**
    $$n_c = \sqrt{n_L}$$

---

## 15. Aberrations
**Spherical Aberration**
* **Bending Factor:**
    $$\sigma = \frac{r_2 + r_1}{r_2 - r_1}$$

**Oblique Astigmatism**
* **Face-Form (Axis 090):**
    $$F_{@090} = F \left( 1 + \frac{\sin^2\theta}{2n} \right)$$
    * **Induced Cylinder (Axis 090):** $F(\tan^2\theta)$
* **Pantoscopic Tilt (Axis 180):**
    $$F_{@180} = F \left( 1 + \frac{\sin^2\theta}{2n} \right)$$
    * **Induced Cylinder (Axis 180):** $F(\tan^2\theta)$

**Chromatic Aberration**
* **Dispersive Power:**
    $$\omega = \frac{n_f - n_c}{n_d - 1}$$
* **Constringence (Abbe Value):**
    $$v = \frac{1}{\omega} = \frac{n_d - 1}{n_f - n_c}$$
* **Lateral Chromatic Aberration:**
    $$\text{Lateral } CA = P_f - P_c = \frac{P_d}{v}$$
* **Longitudinal Chromatic Aberration:**
    $$\text{Longitudinal } CA = F_f - F_c = \frac{F_d}{v}$$
